block main-content
  h1 Pet Care Information
  
  section.intro
    .intro-content
      p Welcome to our comprehensive pet care guide. Whether you're a new pet owner or have years of experience, proper care is essential for your furry friend's health and happiness.

  section.care-tips
    h2 Essential Pet Care Tips
    .tip-grid
      .tip-card
        img(src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1619895092538-128341789043?w=500&auto=format&fit=crop&q=60&ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxzZWFyY2h8Nnx8cGV0JTIwZm9vZHxlbnwwfHwwfHx8MA%3D%3D" alt="Healthy pet food")
        h3 Nutrition
        p Provide a balanced diet appropriate for your pet's age, size, and health condition. Always ensure fresh water is available.

      .tip-card
        img(src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1601758228041-f3b2795255f1?w=500&auto=format&fit=crop&q=60&ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxzZWFyY2h8M3x8ZG9nJTIwcGxheWluZ3xlbnwwfHwwfHx8MA%3D%3D" alt="Dog playing in the park")
        h3 Exercise
        p Regular exercise is crucial for your pet's physical and mental well-being. Aim for at least 30 minutes of activity daily.

      .tip-card
        img(src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1516734212186-a967f81ad0d7?w=500&auto=format&fit=crop&q=60&ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxzZWFyY2h8Mnx8Y2F0JTIwZ3Jvb21pbmd8ZW58MHx8MHx8fDA%3D" alt="Cat being groomed")
        h3 Grooming
        p Regular grooming keeps your pet clean and allows you to check for any skin issues or abnormalities.

      .tip-card
        img(src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1628009368231-7bb7cfcb0def?w=500&auto=format&fit=crop&q=60&ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxzZWFyY2h8N3x8dmV0ZXJpbmFyaWFufGVufDB8fDB8fHww" alt="Pet at veterinary checkup")
        h3 Veterinary Care
        p Schedule regular check-ups and keep vaccinations up to date. Don't hesitate to consult your vet if you notice any changes in your pet's behavior or health.

  section.health-wellness
    h2 Health and Wellness
    .section-content
      p Maintaining your pet's health involves more than just addressing illnesses. It includes:
      ul
        li Regular dental care to prevent gum disease
        li Weight management to avoid obesity-related health issues
        li Mental stimulation through toys and interaction
        li Parasite prevention (fleas, ticks, worms)

  section.behavior-training
    h2 Behavior and Training
    .section-content
      p Understanding and shaping your pet's behavior is key to a harmonious relationship. Consider these points:
      ul
        li Start training early and be consistent
        li Use positive reinforcement techniques
        li Socialize your pet with other animals and people
        li Address behavioral issues promptly, seeking professional help if needed

  section.emergency-care
    h2 Emergency Care
    .section-content
      p Be prepared for emergencies:
      ul
        li Know the location and contact information of your nearest 24-hour veterinary clinic
        li Keep a pet first-aid kit at home
        li Learn to recognize signs of common pet emergencies

